<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06054j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06054j">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06054j"> 54(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> paints her measles</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Cette disposition &agrave; la <font color="green">[= la poup&eacute;e]</font> confondre avec sa propre individualit&eacute; se manifeste de diverses fa&ccedil;ons bien curieuses. &ldquo;Laura Bridgeman &hellip;, une enfant d&eacute;j&agrave; d&apos;un certain &acirc;ge, mettait un bandeau semblable au sien sur les yeux de sa poup&eacute;e. Ce fait rappelle le cas d&apos;une fillette de six ans qui, pendant sa convalescence <mark>de la rougeole</mark>, fut surprise occup&eacute;e &agrave; <mark>peindre sur chacune de ses poup&eacute;es des taches d&apos;un rouge vif</mark>. <font color="green">[This disposition of the doll confused with its own individuality manifests itself in various curious ways. Laura Bridgeman ..., a child already of a certain age, put a headband similar to hers on the eyes of her doll. This fact recalls the case of a six-year-old girl who, during her convalescence of measles, occupied herself painting bright red spots on each of her dolls.]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 126-7</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01125g" href="c01all.htm#c01125g">VI.C.01:125(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
